## One-Click Run
1. **Click “Open in GitHub Codespaces”** (button above).  
2. It will auto-install deps and run **`./run_all.sh`** (see `.devcontainer/postCreateCommand`).  
3. Results appear under each domain folder and `paper/figs/`. CI also runs on pushes.

## What’s here
- **Cosmology (ΛCDM + ta-URT)** — 3D comoving PM (CIC + KDK), Eisenstein–Hu ICs, P(k), ξ(r), FoF halos.
- **Robotics** — cart-pole swing-up & stabilize.
- **Power grid** — Kuramoto synchronization.
- **Epidemiology** — SIR peak & burden shaping.
- **Neural excitability** — FitzHugh–Nagumo coherence shaping.
- **Chaos maps / Plasma** — (stubs) ready to plug existing scripts.
- **Paper** — LaTeX manuscript with auto-build via CI (`paper/main.pdf`).

## Quick start (local)
```bash
python -m venv .venv && source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
bash run_all.sh